wiki.summary: "Lalisa" (stylized in all caps) is the debut single by Thai rapper and singer Lisa, a member of South Korean girl group Blackpink. It was released on September 10, 2021, by YG Entertainment as the lead single from her debut single album of the same name. It is written and produced by long-time YG collaborators Teddy Park along with Bekuh Boom, with additional production handled by 24. Read more on Last.fm.
